A R E S O L U T I O N
In memory of Jack Cera.
WHEREAS, The members of the House of Representatives of the 136th 1
General Assembly of Ohio were deeply saddened to learn of the death of 2
Jack Cera and pay tribute to his memory; and 3
WHEREAS, Jack Cera will be remembered fondly by all those who knew 4
him, and his absence will leave an irreparable void in our society. 5
Widely respected for his tenure with the Ohio General Assembly, he was 6
an advocate for the growth and progress of the State of Ohio and its 7
people, and over the course of his twenty-four years as a legislator 8
with the Ohio House of Representatives, he served as the minority whip 9
and on such important committees as Finance, Ways and Means, 10
Agriculture, Public Utilities, and Natural Resources. Clearly, his 11

