WHEREAS, Without question, Jack Cera made the world much fuller, 23
and he was especially devoted to the individuals who had a treasured 24
relationship with him, including his wife, Becky, his children, Jaclyn 25
and Bethany, and his grandchildren, Scarlett, Lena, and Finley. All 26
those who cherished him can find strength and solace in the happy 27
moments shared with this great man. Most assuredly, the State of Ohio 28
has benefited exponentially from his life’s work, and he will be 29
remembered for his visionary example of citizenship; therefore be it 30
RESOLVED, That we, the members of the House of Representatives of 31
the 136th General Assembly of Ohio, in adopting this Resolution, offer 32
our heartfelt condolences to the family and friends of Jack Cera and 33
express a profound sense of loss and sincere regret on the sorrowful 34
occasion of his death; and be it further 35
RESOLVED, That the Clerk of the House of Representatives transmit 36
a duly authenticated copy of this Resolution to the family of Jack 37
Cera. 38

